what is pem key?
In the context of Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2), a .pem file refers to a file format used to store the private key associated with an EC2 instance. The .pem file is also known as a key pair file.

When you launch an EC2 instance, you have the option to associate a key pair with the instance. A key pair consists of a public key and a private key. The public key is stored on the EC2 instance and is used for authentication, while the private key is downloaded to your local machine in the form of a .pem file.

