How can I add user to server?
Open the Windows Server Essentials Dashboard. On the navigation bar, click Users. In the Users Tasks pane, click Add a user account.

To add a user to your HTTP server, you need to set up basic authentication. Basic authentication is a simple authentication mechanism built into the HTTP protocol that prompts users to enter a username and password when accessing a protected resource. Here's how you can add a user to your HTTP server:

Create a Password File:
The first step is to create a password file that will store the usernames and encrypted passwords for the users you want to grant access to. Apache provides a utility called htpasswd to create and manage this file.

Install htpasswd if it's not already available on your system:

sudo yum install -y httpd

